RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROJO PEQUENO had good speed and dueled to the backstretch, inched away to the second turn, turned back SHILSHOLE BAY into the stretch and held gamely. SHILSHOLE BAY tracked the pace to the second turn, made a run outside the winner to briefly loom a threat into the stretch but was outfinished in the drive. SHOT OF BRANDY stalked the leaders early, was three wide on the second turn and lacked a closing response. RALLIFIED fanned four wide to the backstretch, chased to the second turn then weakened. TREASURE MESA had no speed and was never a threat. SODA SPRINGS hustled early, dueled to the backstretch then gradually gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Rojo Pequeno
ENTRY.COMMENT: good speed, dueled early, inched clear, met bid, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Shilshole Bay
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, rallied 2wide, loomed boldly, outfinished

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Josephine County Juvenile S. GRANTS PASS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 62. Stakes Purse 13000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS. FREE nominations closed Sunday, October 1 with thirteen, or by supplementary nomination of $150 each by closing time of entries. $200 to pass the entry box. First preference to winners. Second preference by total earnings. Field will be limited to ten starters. Weight 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEER BEGONE pressed the pace to the backstretch then pushed to the front, edged away to the second turn then was under steady urging. MONARCA DE ORO set the pace early, was collared on the backstretch then was not threatened for the place. MONTUCKY was outsprinted early, raced two wide and was never a threat. PRIME TIME PORTA trailed throughout.

ENTRY.NAME: Beer Begone
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, bid to lead, clear, driving

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCIPAL SMITH lugged out, corrected, gamely. JR battled, outkicked, 2d best. CPR A AMERICAN EAGLE broke out, bumped, outfinished. EZ COWBOY GAME bumped start, no rally. LA BICHOTA no menace. IMA KNIGHT bumped both sides start. SNIPPY KAREN SUE no speed, pulled up, walked off. PRINCESS K broke out sharply, lost rider.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 7200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200. Oregon Bred Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAMOUS ROCK STAR set all the pace, drew away on the far turn and held driving. SECRET LIFE STYLE had no speed, rallied outside rivals then was four wide to the stretch and closed late for second. MILEYS BLUECAT also had no speed, was roused three deep to the stretch but could only pick off rivals. MYSTIC WOOD FORCE pressed the winner two wide for a half mile then weakened. TUMAC MOUNTAIN was outrun while saving ground to the second turn then came up empty. MR BOTANICALS had no speed and was not a factor. WHATWASITHINKING was four wide early, tracked to the second turn then tired. BRONY BOY was never a threat. FOREVER GOLD stalked the pace for three eighths then gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Secret Life Style
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, bid widest, 4wide 2d turn, late 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Famous Rock Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: best speed, set pace, drew clear, held driving

ENTRY.NAME: Mystic Wood Force
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, off rail, weakened stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 6500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR HY ROLLER pressed the pace two wide, rallied to get on terms into the stretch then battled gamely to edge away. CASH'S CAT set the pace, resisted the winner to the stretch then was bested. COLTON'S TIGER chased the top two, was asked three wide to the stretch then was outfinished and just got the nod for third. NEATAPAR had no speed, swung out four wide while rallying on the far turn then finished with interest. MR MAKUNOUCHI broke slow then saved ground to no avail. SAINT HELEN was five wide throughout and not a threat. POCO DIABLO ROJO had brief speed while four wide but tired after a half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Cash's Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, met bid, responded, bested late

ENTRY.NAME: Our Hy Roller
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, asked 2wide, dueled, dug in gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Makunouchi
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke slow, saved ground to no avail

ENTRY.NAME: Neatapar
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, swung 3-4wide, finished with interest

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 7200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: V BUCKS broke clean an set the pace, saved ground to the stretch then dug in determinedly to hold. SPANISH CHANNEL prompted the winner, bid two wide to the stretch then closed steadily but too late. FANTASTIC SECRET tracked the leaders three wide early, bid two wide to the stretch but could not make an impact. SMILING SALSA drifted inward early crowding ANTECEDENCE, chased the pace from the rail for five furlongs then came up empty. SWEET MEG had no speed, also chased the leaders but saved ground to no avail. FIRE DIAMONDS broke a bit slow, had no speed and was not a factor. ANTECEDENCE was crowded by SMILING SALSA early and took up then tried to bolt the first turn, was under strong restraint and dropped back to last then was outrun. WARNING SOUND had no speed and gave way after a half mile. The jockey on ANTECEDENCE lodged an objection against the rider of SMILING SALSA for alleged interference soon after the start but the stewards made no change to the order of finish.

ENTRY.NAME: Fantastic Secret
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked 3wide, asked 2wide far turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Antecedence
ENTRY.COMMENT: took up early, bore out 1st turn, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Meg
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, chased pace, saved ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Smiling Salsa
ENTRY.OWNER: Root Benjamin Nyland Mike and Amerland Eric
ENTRY.COMMENT: drifted in early, chased pace, saved ground, empty

ENTRY.NAME: V Bucks
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, set pace, saved ground, dug in gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Spanish Channel
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, asked 2wide, steady bid, too late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Grants Pass Distaff S. GRANTS PASS RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Stakes Purse 13600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. FREE nominations closed Sunday, October 1 with nineteen, or by supplementary nomination of $150 each by closing time of entries. $200 to pass the entry box. Preference by total earnings in 2022-2023. Fiel d will be limited to eight starters. Three-Year-Olds 124 lbs.; Older 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IN THE VAULT never far away, rallied three wide after five furlongs, dueled into the stretch then dug in gamely to earn a hard-fought victory. REIGN OF FIRE dueled for the lead throughout, was two wide to the stretch, battled determinedly but was nipped late while holding second. RED NOON RISING stumbled at the start, had no speed, rallied three wide to the stretch then closed willingly but missed. BETHEL RIDGE tracked the pace from the rail, had room but could not get through into the final bend then shifted out for room and closed willingly but too late. CONFIDENCE BUILDER had no speed, was three or four wide but came up empty in the drive. RED NOVA hustled to show speed for a half mile but gave way thereafter. FIRE ESCAPE was four wide and through early.

ENTRY.NAME: Bethel Ridge
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, saved ground, shifted out, steady run, too late

ENTRY.NAME: In the Vault
ENTRY.COMMENT: never far back, bid 3wide, dueled, gamely

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled, off rail far turn, battled, nipped, saved 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Red Noon Rising

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 9 5F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ INDY prompted the pace early, bid two wide to the stretch then closed willingly and was along in time. SPEEDY TOM hustled to the front, set the pace from the rail to the stretch, responded but could not stall the winner. BOB'S SNIPER chased the pace for a half, was fanned four wide to the stretch and was gaining steadily but too late. XTRAFINE XTINA stalked the pace for three furlongs, bid three wide to loom a threat on the second turn then was outfinished in the drive. SIR LAUGHALOT had no speed, was two then three wide and closed belatedly. SKEESIX got outsprnted early, tried to rally three deep but came up empty. CAPITAL EXPENSE hesitated then dropped his head when the gates opened, came out about eight lengths last and did not recover. DIAMOND WILLOW had no speed and was never a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Capital Expense
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated, broke very slow, lost chance

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Indy
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, roused 2wide, steady rally, driving

ENTRY.NAME: Speedy Tom
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled to lead, pace rail, responded late, tagged
